ZH: 我要致以最诚挚的祝福给我的父母。
EN: I want to extend my heartfelt wishes to my parents.

ZH: 感谢你对我们公司的支持，我要向您致以诚挚的谢意。
EN: Thank you for your support to our company, I want to express my sincere gratitude to you.

ZH: 今天是您的生日，我要向您致以最美好的祝福。
EN: Today is your birthday, I want to send you the best wishes.

ZH: 我想致以深深的歉意，因为我没有尽到我的责任。
EN: I want to express my deep apologies as I didn't fulfill my responsibilities.

ZH: 在这里，我想向所有的志愿者致以崇高的敬意。
EN: Here, I want to pay high respect to all the volunteers.

ZH: 请允许我致以崇高的敬意和最真诚的祝福。
EN: Please allow me to extend my high regards and sincerest wishes.

ZH: 示以感谢
EN: Show thanks

ZH: 向他人示以友谊
EN: Show friendship to others

ZH: 他向每位参加者致以问候。
EN: He greeted every participant.

ZH: 当客人离开时，她向他们致以告别。
EN: When the guests left, she bid them farewell.

ZH: 我想向你致以邀请，参加我的生日派对。
EN: I would like to extend an invitation to you to join my birthday party.

ZH: 他向那个干得很好的学生致以祝贺。
EN: He offered congratulations to that student who did well.

ZH: 他向演员致以鼓励的掌声。
EN: He applauded the actor to offer encouragement.

ZH: 我们向遭受这场灾难的人们致以最深切的慰问。
EN: We offer our deepest condolences to those affected by this disaster.

ZH: 在这困难时刻，我向你致以最诚挚的慰问。
EN: In this difficult time, I extend my heartfelt condolences to you.

ZH: 我想向所有为这个项目做出贡献的人致以敬意。
EN: I want to pay tribute to everyone who contributed to this project.

ZH: 学校校长在开学典礼致以热烈的欢迎词。
EN: The school principal delivered a warm welcome speech at the opening ceremony.

ZH: 我要向你表示真诚的感激，并向你致以最美好的祝福。
EN: I want to express my sincere gratitude to you and send you the best wishes.

ZH: 请允许我在此向你致以最真挚的道歉。
EN: Please allow me to offer you my sincerest apologies here.

ZH: 在这个隆重的场合，我要向你们致以最热烈的祝贺。
EN: On this grand occasion, I want to extend my warmest congratulations to all of you.
